review_blob: A decent beer. I can think of many others i would rather drink, but this one is okay when its on sale. A non-distinct nose with a sharp, tart to chemical tasting taste, with lots of carbonation.
I think about the only saving factor for this beer is that it is cheap and it has a high alcohol content, otherwise it tastes like urine.
This beer has a nice flowery/jasminey type of nose with a fairly clean, crisp taste. Its not super memoroable, but it is a nice drinking beer.
This is an easy drinking beer, with a slightly tart taste and metallic/chemical aftertaste. Its good on a hot day when youre parched, but when drunk in quantity it gets a little nasty.

This is a pretty un-aromatic and bland Hef. Not especially sweet or tart on the nose and palate. Everytime i drink this beer i want it to have some exceptional quality, but I dont get it. Just common.
good drinking, anytime beer. Not too pungent, but still has a slightly flowery aroma to it. A beer that you can drink all night and not get filled up on. A little on the pricey side though.
Has a nice fruity-flora head, pours with little foam. Has a nice cloudy appearance, yet is lighter beer than most witbiers. This is a nice change if you are tired of your heavier Hefs.

This may be the perfect bar beer. Its light and easy to drink, has a delightfully creamy tasteful head, and most importantly, tastes like beer from beggining to end, not bananas or whatever. This is good drinking beer.

Tall boys for 99 cents. thats all i got to say. Really though, this is an easy drinking beer that I easily perfer over all other Miller beers. Goes with the BBQ, pizza, late night drink fests, you name it. This beer has no exceptional taste to speak of, besides an average exceptionally expected beer taste.
This is a solid drinking beer for the price.  I cant name a specific attribute that solidley stands-out, yet never disappointed.
This hefe is a classic example of european brewing. My only complaint is that it begins to become too aromatic after drinking a couple.
Its terrible. The only redeeming qualities to speak of are its cheap, you can drink it all day, and because you can drink it all day, it gives you a bit of a buzz.
